-- Russian Hackers Made $4.5 Billion Last Year, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-04-24T04:03:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-24/russian-hackers-made-4-5-billion-last-year-vedomosti-says.html
Russian-speaking hackers made $4.5
billion last year, second only to English-speaking hackers,
 Vedomosti  said, citing research by Group IB.  Internet criminals based in  Russia  made $2.3 billion last
year, while Russian-speaking hackers living abroad made $2.2
billion, an estimated 36 percent of the total market, the
Moscow-based newspaper said, citing the same study.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow at 
